# This directory is git's core.hooksPath (set by `make install-hooks`), so any
# tool that auto-installs hooks drops them here. Notably git-lfs installs four:
# post-checkout, post-commit, post-merge, pre-push. Those are machine-specific
# (like anything in .git/hooks) and managed by the tool, not by us — ignore
# everything except our own tracked hook scripts so they neither clutter
# `git status` nor get committed by accident. LFS keeps working regardless.
*
!.gitignore
!pre-commit
